      "text": "Why does a standard array-based queue suffer from performance issues during removal (dequeue)?",
      "image_url": null,
      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "feedback": {
        "correct": "Precisely. Moving every item to fill the gap at index 0 is what slows the system down.",
        "incorrect": "If you remove the first item in a simple list, what happens to the 'empty hole' at the start? How does the computer fix it?"
